Description: BioModels Database is a reliable repository of computational models of biological processes. It hosts models described in peer-reviewed scientific literature and models generated automatically from pathway resources (Path2Models). A large number of models collected from literature are manually curated and semantically enriched with cross-references from external data resources.BioModels Linked Dataset captures the content of the models in BioModels Database (primarilly encoded in the SBML format) in RDF.
